title: Government’s doubling down on ‘failure’ as energy bills skyrocket
description: Nationals Senator Matt Canavan states the Labor government needs some “self-reflection” as energy bills have increased by “around $1000 per family”.  “Why would you double down on failure?” Mr Canavan told Sky News Australia.  “Everything's being closed down … the only thing the government seems committed to keeping open is our borders.”

title: ‘So incredibly embarrassing’: Prince Harry makes a fool of himself on Stephen Colbert’s show
description: Sky News host Rita Panahi reacts to Prince Harry’s appearance on Stephen Colbert’s show.   “The whole thing was just so incredibly embarrassing,” Ms Panahi said.  “The timing of Harry’s appearance couldn’t have been worse … it was at a time when Meghan Markle’s father was gravely ill, in hospital.”

title: ‘Painful experience’: Labor government under fire for hiding ISIS bride involvement
description: Strategic analysis Australia Director Peter Jennings slams the Labor government for not being transparent about their involvement in bringing the ISIS brides to Australia.  “The government is being exceptionally clever in how it goes about trying to say it had nothing to do with it,” Mr Jennings told Sky News host Peta Credlin.  “They seem to be collaborating quite effectively with a non-government organisation to allow it to happen.  “We go through the very painful experience of watching senior bureaucrats at senate committee meetings all of a sudden being unable to remember meetings that they actually attended.”

title: Prime Minister pays tribute to the ‘remarkable’ Graham Richardson
description: Prime Minister Anthony Albanese pays tribute to Graham Richardson in a eulogy that honoured his “unparalleled political instincts”.  “A role in which he channelled his remarkable energy, focus and persistence into championing the protection of Australia's natural heritage … protection that included saving the Daintree,” Mr Albanese said.   “He was never one to consider losing as a valid option.”

title: ‘Deeply damaging to democracy’: Labor slammed for limiting freedom of information
description: Strategic analysis Australia Director Peter Jennings is disappointed in the Labor Party’s secrecy.  “The fact that we now have to pay to have access to freedom of information, it’s no longer free,” Mr Jennings told Sky News host Peta Credlin.   “At every state and in every way, this government is trying to hold back or contain information.  “It’s deeply damaging to democracy and making good policy.”

title: Sydney Sweeney opens up about brutal American Eagle backlash
description: Sky News host Rita Panahi says Sydney Sweeney’s backlash for her jeans ad was “enormously successful for American Eagle”.   “She was abused online for the campaign, some calling her a white supremacist,” Ms Panahi said.   “She told People magazine she was surprised by the reaction.  “In a way, it’s not bad for her brand.”

title: Joyce gave ‘fair warning’ he would quit the ‘deficient’ Nationals
description: One Nation Chief of Staff James Ashby claims New England MP Barnaby Joyce gave “fair warning” to the National Party that he was leaving.  “I know you’re upset, but take your aggression out on the right people, and that is the Liberal and National parties,” Mr Ashby told Sky News host Peta Credlin.  “They're the ones that are deficient in policy, and One Nation is leading the charge.”

title: 'Outrage’ after BBC plants illegal migrants in the audience to garner sympathy
description: Sky News contributor Sophie Elsworth calls out the BBC for planting illegal immigrants in the audience as a way to attack UK Reform Leader Nigel Farage’s agenda.   “There's been a lot of outrage over this that these illegal migrants were planted deliberately in the audience so that the British public would sympathise with their case,” Ms Elsworth told Sky News host Chris Kenny.   “The hits on Nigel Farage, the Reform UK leader they just keep on coming. They will not stop trying to attack him.”

title: Sydney Sweeney ‘sets record straight’ on left's meltdown over American Eagle ad
description: ‘Kinsey Schofield Unfiltered’ host Kinsey Schofield hopes Sydney Sweeney’s comments on her American Eagle ad “shut down” any further backlash she receives.    “I hate that Sydney Sweeney even has to address baseless rumours, but sometimes those narratives take on a life of their own,” Ms Schofield told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “She chose to step in, set the record straight. I respect that.”

title: New revelations about Jay Z’s infamous fight with Beyonce’s sister exposed
description: Sky News host Rita Panahi reveals new details about Jay Z and Solange Knowles’ “infamous elevator fight”.   “Surveillance footage from inside that elevator at New York City Standard Hotel showed Solange lunging at, swinging at and kicking Jay Z,” Ms Panahi said.  “Beyonce just stood by and watched that assault happen … she was just observing.  “Now fashion designer Oscar G Lopez … claims Jay Z complimented [Rachel] Roy’s dress at the event and that’s what set off this chain reaction.”

title: Beyonce’s sister goes crazy over Jay Z’s infamous infidelity
description: ‘Kinsey Schofield Unfiltered’ host Kinsey Schofield says she is not “buying” Oscar G Lopez’s claims about the real reason why Jay Z and Solange Knowles had their infamous fight in a New York City hotel elevator.   “I’m not buying it,” Ms Schofield told Sky News host Rita Panahi.   “We knew the fight was about infidelity ... and it’s Becky with the good hair.”

title: Prince Harry lives in a ‘gig economy’ after jumping from show to show to make money
description: ‘Kinsey Schofield Unfiltered’ host Kinsey Schofield claims Prince Harry’s appearance on Stephen Colbert’s show portrays him as “not on a steady income”.   “Prince Harry’s reality is that he is living in a gig economy now, hustling from one paid project to the next,” Ms Schofield told Sky News host Rita Panahi.   “His income depends on Americans buying his shows, books and speaking engagements.”

title: ‘Transactional’ Meghan blasted for sending ill father email after he begged to see her
description: Sky News host Rita Panahi slams Meghan Markle for sending an email to her father, who was “gravely ill” in hospital.   “The Sun newspaper has revealed that the Duchess of Sussex has sent her estranged father an email,” Ms Panahi said.  “He has begged Meghan to see him before he dies.  “An email, really? You couldn’t even send a message to the hospital.  “It is just so transactional and lacking in feeling.”

title: ‘The time has come’: Australia failing to prepare for nuclear technology
description: Strategic Analysis Australia Director Peter Jennings believes Australia needs to lift its defence spending immediately.   “I think that it is going to be a very tough meeting,” Mr Jennings told Sky News host Peta Credlin.  “There are many, many areas that we are just failing to, with sufficient speed, gear up to be able to take on that nuclear technology.  “Our government has fought against that, but the time has now come.”

title: ‘Sneakiest way possible’: Labor’s private meetings with a non-government organisation
description: Strategic analysis Australia Director Peter Jennings criticises Minister for Home Affairs of Australia Tony Burke for holding private meetings with a non-government organisation.   “Typically, what ministers and prime ministers want is they want officials in the room to keep an honest record of what’s going on,” Mr Jennings told Sky News host Peta Credlin.  “Can a minister actually have a private conversation with a non-government organisation?  “It really shouldn’t be allowed to happen.  “It’s chosen however, to do it in the sneakiest way possible.”
